Model.name: Optimization of isoprene production via MEP pathway of Arabidopsis thaliana
Model.Comment:
Kinetic model of extended MEP pathway in Arabidopsis thaliana for cis-abienol production.
This model was used for determining total optimization potential (TOP) of cis-abienol production in Arabidopsis thaliana using Spacescanner (https://github.com/atiselsts/spacescanner). This model was used to make designs A, B and C. An optimization task in COPASI can be perfomed using this model by accesing COPASI/Tasks/Optimization. Parameters which will be changed during the optimization and the optimization constraints can be selected.
More description in Total optimization potential (TOP) approach based constrained design of isoprene and cis-abienol production in A. thaliana, Authors: Katrina D. Neiburga, Reinis Muiznieks, Darta M. Zake, Agris Pentjuss, Vitalijs Komasilovs, Johann Rohwer, Alain Tissier, Egils Stalidzans
